\frac{1}{k}\sum_{m=r}^{k-1}\frac{m!}{(m-r)!}=\frac{(k-1)(k-2)\ldots(k-r)}{r+1};\quad r=1,2,\ldots
\frac{1}{k}\sum_{m=r}^{k-1}\frac{m!}{(m-r)!}=\frac{1}{k}\sum_{m=r}^{k-1}\frac{m(m-1)\ldots(m-r-1)(m-r)!}{(m-r)!}
\frac{1}{k}\sum_{m=r}^{k-1}\frac{m!}{(m-r)!}=\frac{1}{k}[\frac{r! }{0!}+\frac{(r+1)!}{1!}+\ldots+\frac{(k-1)!}{(k-1-r)!}]
\frac{1}{k} \sum\limits_{m = r}^{k - 1} \frac{m!}{(m - r)!} = \frac{(k - 1)!}{(k - r - 1)! (r + 1)}
